# Services Guide

Service files should handle business logic and data management:

1. Keep services focused on a single responsibility
2. Use async/await for asynchronous operations
3. Implement proper error handling
4. Use SharedPreferences for data persistence
5. Keep services independent from UI components
6. Document public methods with clear comments
7. Return meaningful error messages
8. Implement singleton pattern for services when appropriate

Example service implementation:
```dart
import 'dart:convert';
import 'package:shared_preferences/shared_preferences.dart';
import '../models/mission.dart';

class StorageService {
  static const String _missionsKey = 'missions';
  
  // Singleton pattern
  static final StorageService _instance = StorageService._internal();
  factory StorageService() => _instance;
  StorageService._internal();
  
  /// Saves a mission to local storage
  Future<bool> saveMission(Mission mission) async {
    try {
      final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
      final missions = await getMissions();
      
      // Update existing or add new
      final index = missions.indexWhere((m) => m.id == mission.id);
      if (index >= 0) {
        missions[index] = mission;
      } else {
        missions.add(mission);
      }
      
      // Save to storage
      final missionJsonList = missions.map((m) => jsonEncode(m.toJson())).toList();
      return await prefs.setStringList(_missionsKey, missionJsonList);
    } catch (e) {
      print('Error saving mission: $e');
      return false;
    }
  }
  
  /// Retrieves all missions from local storage
  Future<List<Mission>> getMissions() async {
    try {
      final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
      final missionJsonList = prefs.getStringList(_missionsKey) ?? [];
      
      return missionJsonList
          .map((jsonStr) => Mission.fromJson(jsonDecode(jsonStr)))
          .toList();
    } catch (e) {
      print('Error getting missions: $e');
      return [];
    }
  }
}
```